These comments related to Mud Lake but the data entered in the database are for my usual Koshkonong location- DH.  This is duplicate data for 9/21/2015 because I couldn't figure out how to edit the original data to add my comments.

column1: I was unable to get into Mud Lake itself because it was too shallow for my kayak.  I kayaked from Koshkonong into the stream leading from Mud Lake and took a reading in what seemed to be the deepest part of the stream.  Its GPS was 42 54 06 north and 88 54 38 west.  It is slightly upstream from the concrete supports for the old carp gates.  The Secchi clarity was greater than 1.75 feet- where the disk hit the bottom.  The Koshkonong gauge height was 6.40 feet so if I return in the spring with a gauge height of over 7 feet I should be able to get into the lake.  There was a a significant current toward Koshkonong.

column2: slight algae- breeze from south- clear day
windy today- very windy yesterday.  water low due to winter draw down but even lower yesterday.

clear- calm- NW breeze- much 1 inch algae rods but not clumped.
Hot- humid- cloudy.  No algae- saw about 260 pelicans where mud lake flows into Koshkonong-

clear- slight breeze from north- no algae.  Several "bugs" about 1 cm long swimming below surface.

No wind- very calm water.  1/4" string-like algae.  Surface had what appeared to be many 1" long "husks" perhaps shed from damsel fly nymphs. Large flock of pelicans on shore near Mud Lake.  Tried to get close to them but bottomed out and bent propeller at GPS 42/53/48 N; 88/55/03 W.
